 him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs David de Aberchirder was born about 1333, in Scotland as the daughter of Aberchirder. She married Sir David de Aberchirder about 1365, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1333–":"umbes 1333–Surnud","1333–Female":"1333–Surnud","1333–1365":"1333–1365","1365–1448":"1365–1448","–Male":"Surnud","1448":"1448","1333":"1333","1365":"1365","about 1365":"umbes 1365","about 1333":"umbes 1333","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1333–":"noin 1333–Kuollut","1333–Female":"1333–Kuollut","1333–1365":"1333–1365","1365–1448":"1365–1448","–Male":"Kuollut","1448":"1448","1333":"1333","1365":"1365","about 1365":"noin 1365","about 1333":"noin 1333","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1333–":"environ 1333–Décédée","1333–Female":"1333–Décédée","1333–1365":"1333–1365","1365–1448":"1365–1448","–Male":"Décédé","1448":"1448","1333":"1333","1365":"1365","about 1365":"environ 1365","about 1333":"environ 1333","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs David de Aberchirder est née environ 1333, à Écosse, fille de Aberchirder. Elle a épousé Sir David de Aberchirder environ 1365, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1333–":"um 1333–Verstorben","1333–Female":"1333–Verstorben","1333–1365":"1333–1365","1365–1448":"1365–1448","–Male":"Verstorben","1448":"1448","1333":"1333","1365":"1365","about 1365":"um 1365","about 1333":"um 1333","Abe